abstract: >-
  An exploration of quantum computing concepts through the lens of 
  consciousness and identity persistence, developed via AI-assisted 
  learning. The framework demonstrates how quantum error correction 
  principles can be applied to both philosophical questions about 
  consciousness and practical engineering problems in quantum network 
  optimization. This work maps consciousness persistence through 
  death/rebirth to information fidelity in quantum communication 
  networks, achieving 99.9% fidelity across 11,000km with optimal 
  error correction protocols.
